The Very first thing I should say is What an Action is?
  An action is ANYTHING that a group does.  At the start of each
  turn each player's group's actions are cleared.  Each group
  (i.e. Archers, Footment, Wizards etc) may perform on ACT, such
  as moving, firing, jumping in terrain, etc.  Using such cards
  as Earthquake and Forest Fire count as actions against wizards
  and footmen respectively.  A group CANNOT play more than one
  action per turn.  When a group plays an action a red flashing
  * will appear next to the group letter.  If none is there
  they have yet to play an action.

