 Your first notice will be what the heck is Archers, Footmen, Wizards,
 Knights, Dragons....
   Archers:  These guys are the range shooters.  They are pretty decent
   at ranges 2-3.  Any closer or further away they loose their
   effectiveness.  At close range they are worthless as attackers.

   Footmen:  These are the backbone of the army.  The cannon fodder.
   Footmen are usually the ones to get close in and do the dirty work
   of disposing of the enemy at close range.

   Wizards:  These people are like archers.  They are best at ranges
   2-4 and can cast a variety of spells, dependent upon the cards.
   Such spells as Earthquake and Smoke are very helpful in making
   an enemy fall to their knees.

   Knights:  These are like the Footmen except they are stronger
   and harder to kill.

   Dragons:  The most powerful piece of fighting machine.  Deadly
   at close range, and even worst of all, deadly in quantity.  A player
   possessing a pair of these monsters should be stopped before they
   burn an opponent to a crisp!

